 JOHANNESBURG - Proteas coach Mark Boucher has been charged with gross misconduct by Cricket South Africa. This follows findings contained in the SJN project report, that looked into the lack of transformation in local cricket. READ: WATCH: The way forward for CSA In the hearings, Boucher had allegations of discrimination levelled at him, by former Proteas spinner Paul Adams during the duos playing days. The report also questioned his appointment to the Proteas top job which appeared to flout CSA’s hiring processes. Advocate Terry Motau has been appointed to investigate the claims against Boucher. The former wicketkeeper was presented with a charge sheet on Monday. Parties involved are expected to meet on 26 January to formalise a timeline of action.